Section 10
 Lecture 7: Spring Data JPA CRUD Repositories


1. Create new package: ej.springframework.repositories
 1.1 Create New Interface: ej.springframework.repositories.ProductRepository.java

2. Modify Spring Configuration
 2.1 Add @EnableJpaRepository() annotation to use the Spring JPA Repository

3. Implements CRUD Services
 3.1 Create New service package: ej.springframework.services.reposervices
 3.2 Create and implements new service class: ej.springframework.services.reposervices.ProductServiceRepoImpl.java
 3.3 Add @Service and multiple @Profile annotations on the ProductServiceRepoImpl class
 3.4 Add ProductRepository property
 3.5 Create setter based DI using the @Autowired annotation
 3.6 Implements ProductService methods
 3.7 Modify ej.springframework.services.jpaservices.ProductServiceJpaDaoImpl.java to apply don't use profile
 3.8 Run and connect H2 Database --> Check the PRODUCT Table

